               <msContents>
                  <summary>The Ms. contains only one text:
 I) Maṣḥafa ʾAslǝṭi, Lectionary for
                     the entire year (fols. 5ra-67ra)
 I-1) Scriptural readings for liturgical
                     periods, fasts and feasts for the entire year (fols. 5ra-67ra) 
 -
                     Liturgical period Yoḥannǝs: fols. 5ra-7va
 - Feasts of the Martyrs
                     (Samāʿtāt): fols. 7va-8va
 - Liturgical period Masqal: fols. 25va-27rb
                     - Feasts of the Righteous Ones (Ṣādǝqān): fols. 10rb-11va
 - Liturgical
                     period Ṣǝge: fols. 11va-13ra
 - Feast of the stay of the Holy Family at
                     Mount Qosqam in Egypt and feast of Mary (Qʷǝsqʷām): fols. 13ra-16va
 -
                     Feast of Archangel Michael (Qǝddus Mikāʾel): fols. 16va-18vb
 - Feast of
                     the harvest (Maʿǝrar): fol. 18vb-19vb
 - Liturgical period Sǝbkat: fols.
                     19vb-21rb
 - Liturgical period Bǝrhan: fols. 21rb-22va
 - Liturgical
                     period Nolāwi: fols. 22va-24ra
 - Liturgical period Lǝdat: fols.
                     24ra-25va
 - Feast of the Circumcision (Gǝzrat): fols. 25va-27ra
 -
                     Feast of the Epiphany (Ṭǝmqat): fols. 27ra-29ra
 - Feasts of the Righteous
                     Ones (Ṣādǝqān): fols. 29ra-30va
 - Feast of Simeon, Presentation of the
                     Lord (Sǝmʿon): fols. 30va-34va
 - Week of Nicodemus (Niqodimos) and feast
                     of the Archangel Gabriel (Qǝddus Gabrǝʾel): fols. 34va-36va
 - Palm Sunday
                     (Hosāʿǝnā): fols. 36va-38rb
 - Maundy Thursday (Ṣalota Ḫamus):
                     fols.38rb-43ra
 - Vigil of Easter (maḫatǝwa Fāsikā): fols. 43ra-44va
 -
                     Easter (Fāsikā): fols. 44va-47ra
 - Sunday after Easter (ʾAgbǝʾota Gǝbǝr or
                     Faṣṣamna): fols. 47ra-48va
 - Pentecost (Ṗanṭaqosṭe or Ṗārāqliṭos): fols.
                     48va-50rb
 - Ascension (ʿƎrgat): fols. 50rb-51vb
 - Pentecost
                     (Ṗārāqliṭos): fols. 51vb-54ra
 - Liturgical period Kǝramt (“Rainy season”):
                     fols. 54ra-56rb
 - Fast of the Apostles (Ḥawāryāt): fols. 56rb-57rb
 -
                     Feasts of the Virgin (Dǝngǝl): fols. 57rb-59rb
 - Transfiguration (Dabra
                     Tābor): fols. 59rb-61ra
 - Feast of Abraham (ʾAbrǝham): fols.
                     61ra-62vb
 I-2) Scriptural readings for Hours of Sunday (fols.
                     62vb-67ra)
 
 Additio 1</summary>
